comments: All of it was difficult. I don't know if I'm having a bad day or what. I'm usually pretty decent at finding patterns and solving puzzles and for whatever reason I just had a hard time grasping this. I found a generalization in the different words, although I misspelled most of them. I never knew I would have such an issue grasping this. Maybe its because the words all sound the same for the same for each object with zero descriptor. For example I am used to saying "yellow pentagon" that's a specific description of the object. I believe that would be considered a buvykoh (probably misspelled). The same exact sounding word used for multiple objects with a change of trait (color) was super difficult for me to grasp. Was it supposed to be this difficult? I don't know.
